##Li Wenliang's wife speaks

Micro Signal NDDAILY

Feature presentation, Nandu, in a different way

In the early hours of February 7, the Wuhan Central Hospital announced that Li Wenliang, a "trained Wuhan doctor, " died at 2:58 on February 7.

At 16:39 on February 8, Li Wenliang's wife's verified Weibo Account,@fu Xuejie, issued a statement saying that as of 16:00 on February 8, it had received partial payments due from the four channels in accordance with the law; No contributions have been received from any other individuals or groups. At the same time, it said, "I did not release any information of any nature, nor did I authorize other people to release relevant information or accept donations. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In a public statement on Feb. 8, Fu Xuejie, Li's wife, responded to recent online messages about donations or donations received by Li's family.

The statement said it would accept payments from only four channels, they are: "The state according to law and regulations to Li Wenliang work injury, funeral, and other related compensation payments; Li Wenliang Work Unit (Wuhan Central Hospital) and my work unit (Wuhan Aier Eye Hospital Group Company Limited) help payments; Li Wenliang before his death in accordance with the law to buy insurance payments; government departments recognized or authorized public welfare units (including insurance) set in accordance with the law to fight against the epidemic within the scope of all medical personnel public welfare funds or awards, as part of Li Wenliang as a medical personnel in accordance with the law" .

According to the statement, as at 1600 hours on 8 February 2020, it had received a portion of the money due from the above-mentioned channels for compensation in accordance with the law; it had not received contributions from any other individuals or organizations. At the same time, it said it "persistently refuses to accept any form of money or donations from individuals or groups or institutions other than those mentioned above" . In addition, the statement also shows that, "I do not approve and have no relationship with any of the recent online donations to Li Wenliang, which were made by the publishers themselves. I have not issued a request for assistance of any nature, nor have I authorized any other person to publish such information or to accept donations."

In the early hours of February 7, Wuhan Central Hospital announced that Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at the hospital, died at 2:58 a.m. on February 7 after being infected in an outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia, the hospital deeply regrets and mourns.

On February 7, with the approval of the Central Committee, the State Supervision Commission sent an investigation team to Wuhan, Hubei Province, to conduct a comprehensive investigation into the public's complaints about Li Wenliang. On February 8, the investigation team of the State Supervision Commission arrived in Wuhan.

According to reports by the Hubei Voice and People's Daily, Guanwei, etc. , on February 7, the Wuhan Municipal People's Association Department determined that Li Wenliang, as a medical worker, had contracted pneumonia during the fight against COVID-19 infection and died after rescue efforts were unsuccessful, it's a work injury. The industrial injury insurance benefits are 785,020 yuan for one-time death benefits and 368,340 yuan for funeral benefits, which have already been allocated.

By Southern Metropolis Daily

Interview and writing: Mao Shujie, nandu reporter
